    <title>*** Email Council at council&amp;#064;bouldercolorado.gov to weigh...</title>
    <updated>2020-09-12T19:11:41-06:00</updated>
    <id>https://www.facebook.com/DenverHomelessOutLoud/posts/1990450664418210</id>
    <content type="html">&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/DenverHomelessOutLoud/&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-1/cp0/p50x50/12645267_765701936893095_4336088808811260721_n.png?_nc_cat=106&amp;_nc_sid=dbb9e7&amp;_nc_ohc=afYYDCEOzbwAX-Xa3r1&amp;_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna&amp;oh=cbdd59bdc7cab2b52fe3fbf4777ab1cd&amp;oe=5F85E6BE&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/DenverHomelessOutLoud/&#34;&gt;Denver Homeless Out Loud&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/DenverHomelessOutLoud/posts/1990450664418210&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com&#34;&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;*** Email Council at council&amp;#064;bouldercolorado.gov to weigh in on this topic ***&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Five people went to the hospital to be treated for frostbite in the storm that just came through. Another died. All this, predictably, under a changing regime in which severe weather shelter services were provided at the Boulder Shelter for the Homeless, but lacking the traditional communications that made such service-availability clear to those who need it. Calls to the Boulder Shelter, prior to ...the cold weather, resulted in staff telling the caller that there would be no severe weather shelter provided.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; This death was preventable. People suffering frostbite and going to the hospital was preventable. Who knows how many suffered but didn&#39;t make it to get medical care.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &#34;The man, who was not named, was found unresponsive Wednesday morning in the parking lot of Unity Church, 2855 Folsom. Paramedics and fire responded and administered CPR before transporting the man to Boulder Community Health, where he was pronounced dead.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; “Boulder Community Hospital believes the male died of cold weather exposure, as his core body temp was 75 degrees,” the blotter item reads. An investigation is ongoing.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; The temperature Tuesday night into Wednesday dropped to 30. Boulder received 4 inches of snow overnight, the Daily Camera reported.&#34;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/DenverHomelessOutLoud/posts/1990450664418210&#34;&gt;See More&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://boulderbeat.news/2020/09/12/57-year-old-man-dies-in-boulder-snowstorm/&#34;&gt;Boulder officials believe the death of a likely unhoused man, found near his camp, was a result of exposure to cold weather.&lt;img src=&#34;https://external.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/safe_image.php?d=AQB7VCKCe59bR9mN&amp;w=540&amp;h=282&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fboulderbeat.news%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2FIMG_20200811_090753920.jpg&amp;cfs=1&amp;upscale=1&amp;fallback=news_d_placeholder_publisher&amp;_nc_cb=1&amp;_nc_hash=AQASNvBRb67E_Au4&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; width=&#34;500&#34; height=&#34;262&#34; caption=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;boulderbeat.news&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Police blotter: 57-year-old unhoused man dies during Boulder snowstorm&lt;/p&gt;Boulder officials believe the death of a likely unhoused man, found near his camp, was a result of exposure to cold weather.&lt;a href=&#34;https://boulderbeat.news/2020/09/12/57-year-old-man-dies-in-boulder-snowstorm/&#34;&gt;Boulder officials believe the death of a likely unhoused man, found near his camp, was a result of exposure to cold weather.&lt;/a&gt;</content>
