    <content type="html">&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/DenverHomelessOutLoud/&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-1/cp0/p50x50/12645267_765701936893095_4336088808811260721_n.png?_nc_cat=106&amp;_nc_sid=dbb9e7&amp;_nc_ohc=afYYDCEOzbwAX-Xa3r1&amp;_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna&amp;oh=cbdd59bdc7cab2b52fe3fbf4777ab1cd&amp;oe=5F85E6BE&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/DenverHomelessOutLoud/&#34;&gt;Denver Homeless Out Loud&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/DenverHomelessOutLoud/photos/a.271630356300258/1983182198478390/&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com&#34;&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;Likely First Snow on Tuesday - Survival Gear Needed&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; It is supposed to snow and be a high of 37 on Tuesday. This will be a sudden drop from 91 the day before. This is a recipe for danger for those living without housing. If you can donate a tent, tarp, sleeping bag, blanket, coat, soaks, or hand warmers folks can use this gear! Bring these items to our office on Monday at 2260 California St between 9am and 5pm. Or give them directly to people you know who need them. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; This is t...he same day as a sweep is planned for the camp at 25th and Arapahoe. Will the city really take peoples only blankets, tents, ect as it is snowing and freezing and scatter folks to nowhere with nothing to cover oneself??? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Contact the Mayor and demand he find a heart. &lt;br /&gt; Email -  mayorsoffice&amp;#064;denvergov.org&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Contact:&lt;br /&gt; info&amp;#064;denverhomelessoutloud.org&lt;br /&gt; 720-940-5291&lt;/p&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/DenverHomelessOutLoud/posts/1983182298478380&#34;&gt;See More&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/DenverHomelessOutLoud/photos/a.271630356300258/1983182198478390/&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-0/p